      "content": "The worst that could happen with combining them is an exaggerated \"knockout\" effect, leading to grogginess, dizziness, or feeling like you've been hit by a truck the next day. Since you are so exhausted, I recommend taking the zolpidem as directed and perhaps having a very small, measured dose of melatonin about an hour before, but *never* more than the dosage on the bottle. If you feel any unusual heavy sedation, you must stop and call your pharmacist immediately.",
